      "description": "This build features sustain and damage, which lets Alpha attack and defend while battle spells can be changed from petrify to arrival because petrify can stun, which can let Alpha connect & chain combos, while arrival can finish off sets made by the tank. \n\nFor the emblems, the fighter enhances the spell vamp and pairs well with the Festival of Blood. For vitality, this makes Alpha have increased maxHP, which makes him last longer in teamfights. Temporal Reign reduced the cooldown of the first 2 skills when the ultimate is used, which can let Alpha spam, and since his ultimate activates frequently, this pair passes well with Alpha's ultimate. \n\nFor the first item, magic boots porvides 10% cooldown reduction and increased health. \n\nThe second item Hunter Strike can chase due to the movement speed provided, and the damage penetration is high with an 10% cooldown reduction, which pairs well with Alpha's 2nd skill. \n\nFor the third item, Oracle is chosen because of the magic and physical damage it provides, and 30% morechealing and shields for Alpha, which pairs well with Alpha's skill 2. \n\nFor the fourth it,  it is Sky Piercer, so that Alpha can finish off low HP enemies. This pairs well with his skill one and ultimate. \n\nThe fifth Queen's Wings, because of the 10% cooldown reduction + 10% spell vamp. Queen's Wings also includes adaptive damage and increases maxHP. When alpha is low HP, it gives increased damage, damage reduction, and decreased cooldown for 2 seconds, which goes with Oracle, Sky Piercer, Temporal Reign, Festival of Blood, and Vitality.\n\nThe last item, Blade of Despair, provides serious damage, amplifying the effect of burst and sustain. This connects and synergizes with the emblems and the previous 5 items.  ",
